<bug>
	<id>89249</id>
	<title>LibreOffice crashes when using fields in a template made in an older version of LibreOffice...</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">When opening a self made template with custom fields made in an earlier version of LibreOffice Writer, the program crashes when clicking "next" for the following custom field.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.2">This doesn't happen when the template is made in LibreOffice 4.4.0.3 itself.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.3">But when opening a template made in an earlier version of LibreOffice, it crashes immediately when entering the next field in the document.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">I couldn't reproduce the same behaviour in LibreOffice 4.2.8, which we use at the office.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.2">In this version it works fine.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
